keep.name: Charleston
keep.description: This booth has been marked as inactive. Photos: January 22, 2010. Thanks to Anthony for telling us about the Model 20, newly installed in the Charleston, "centrally located between Shakespeare and Dickens in the heart of Bucktown." As Anthony says, "This booth's former home was on the boardwalk in Ocean City, Maryland. The sign is (supposedly) from the Texas State Fair." UPDATE 1/13/11: This booth is no longer located at the Charleston, but has moved to the state of Ohio, to the Massillon Museum in Massillon.

keep.name: The Florida Room
keep.description: This booth has been marked as inactive. Photos: March 23, 2010. MAP: [Google Maps](http://maps.google.com/maps?oi=map&q=435%20North%20Killingsworth%20Street%20Portland%20Oregon&sll=45.563068,-122.670807) WEB: [MySpace](http://www.myspace.com/teamevil3). Victoria writes, "In the very back room by the pool table I had a small battle with this booth and lost. Both strips came out streaky and the second had big spots where the photo didn't even develop so I gave up. There were two girls there and they told me they had had problems with the booth that night too but they used this particular booth somewhat regularly and it normally gave them good results. My friend Lauren and I picked some dandelions and I would have kept redoing the shot until we got it right but the photos were coming out so bad it was a lost cause." UPDATE 7/12/15: Sam reports that "the long-time awesome photobooth at the Florida Room was replaced with a digital photobooth a couple weeks ago. Another one bites the dust." Contributed by Victoria Jarvis, Sam Loper.

keep.description: According to Greg, the WAB is a microbrewery, open until 2am most days. UPDATE 4/4/13: Jody wrote to let us know that this booth is no longer located at the WAB. 'An employee said they fixed it a couple of time. Parts fell out and too much trouble and hassle to keep it up and running. The staff at this place admitted they do miss photo booth very much.'
